snippet.title: The Offspring - Gone Away | Soul AI Cover
snippet.description:
Gone Away by The Offspring twisted into Soul Music

Like what you hear? Help keep the party going!
https://tiptopjar.com/TwistedMusicStudio

Lyrics:

Maybe in another life
I could find you there
Pulled away before your time
I can't deal, it's so unfair

And it feels, and it feels like
Heaven is so far away
And it feels, yeah, it feels like
The world has grown cold
Now that you've gone away

Leaving flowers on your grave
Show that I still care
Black roses and "Hail Marys"
Can't bring back what's taken from me

I reach to the sky and call out your name
And if I could trade, I would

And it feels, and it feels like
Heaven is so far away
And it stings, yeah, it stings, now
The world is so cold
Now that you've gone away

Gone away, gone away

Yeah ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh, oh yeah

I'll save your soul, whoa
Yeah, yeah-oh, ooh-ooh

I reach to the sky and call out your name
Oh, please let me trade, I would

And it feels, and it feels like
Heaven is so far away
And it feels, yeah, it feels like
The world has grown cold
Now that you've gone away
